00:42:58.120 --> 00:43:07.230
This is from chapter three; it's about pleading the blood in case they want to find it.

00:43:07.230 --> 00:43:21.587
I once heard a speaker—speak up real loud if you can—who had been a spiritualist pastor for nearly 20 years before he was saved.

00:43:30.212 --> 00:43:30.456
The man said he was sincere and honest; he just didn't know about Jesus.

00:43:34.160 --> 00:43:35.640
He said that they had all of the gifts of the Spirit in counterfeit in his church.

00:43:35.640 --> 00:43:42.240
If the devil was going to set up a counterfeit church, naturally, he'd pattern it after God's genuine church.

00:43:42.240 --> 00:43:51.100
'We sang the same songs that you sing in Christian churches,' the man said.

00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:55.594
'But there was one thing that bothered me.

00:43:55.594 --> 00:44:02.955
We could sing about the blood of Jesus or the name of Jesus.

00:44:02.955 --> 00:44:09.359
But when we began to sing, "There's power in the blood," those spirits got agitated.

00:44:09.359 --> 00:44:10.285
' Yes.

00:44:10.285 --> 00:44:13.400
Jesus said, 'In my name, they'll cast out devils.

00:44:13.400 --> 00:44:28.060
' But did you ever stop to think that the power behind it all is based on the blood?

00:44:28.060 --> 00:44:36.600
You must take the whole Word of God, not just part of it, to rightly divide the word with this truth.

00:44:36.600 --> 00:44:44.160
When I came into Full Gospel circles, I remember they were always talking about pleading the blood.

00:44:46.667 --> 00:45:00.850
I didn't know what they were talking about until I began to examine the scriptures on the subject, and I noticed one thing in particular: when they did, they got results.

00:45:05.320 --> 00:45:05.577
You can't argue with success.

00:45:13.840 --> 00:45:14.120
About this same time, I read a testimony published in a Full Gospel periodical.

00:45:31.809 --> 00:45:32.004
The author was a woman missionary who had been left behind in a native village to take care of the church while the other missionaries were away.

00:45:32.004 --> 00:45:40.180
She went to the main part of that village and said she was examining some goods when a scorpion stung her.

00:45:40.180 --> 00:45:45.165
She was out on the street when it fastened itself to her hand.

00:45:45.165 --> 00:45:52.010
So many of the people saw this.

00:45:52.010 --> 00:46:00.066
She said, 'I just shook it off and said, "In the name of Jesus, I plead the blood.

00:46:00.066 --> 00:46:09.700
"' Did you ever stop to think that the name of Jesus wouldn't work if it weren't for the blood?

00:46:25.983 --> 00:46:26.217
It all goes together.

00:46:28.846 --> 00:46:40.570
The missionary noticed that everyone was watching her, waiting for her to die because no one ever survived the sting of that kind of scorpion.

00:46:40.570 --> 00:46:44.410
There was no antidote for it either.

00:46:44.410 --> 00:46:51.719
But the missionary just went her way, walking back toward the little mission church.

00:47:01.406 --> 00:47:01.691
The whole village followed, still waiting for her to fall over dead.

00:47:01.691 --> 00:47:02.834
But nothing happened.

00:47:02.834 --> 00:47:09.160
She went inside the church and the villagers thronged after her.

00:47:09.160 --> 00:47:14.640
In fact, they couldn't all fit in the church.

00:47:14.640 --> 00:47:23.650
Since the church was full, the missionary decided to hold a service.

00:47:23.650 --> 00:47:32.100
Even though it was in the middle of the afternoon, she was never affected by the scorpion sting.

00:47:32.100 --> 00:47:35.910
She said, 'In the name of Jesus, I plead the blood against this.

00:47:35.910 --> 00:47:45.420
' You see, her understanding of the blood was a little different from most people's.

00:47:45.420 --> 00:47:51.368
So, I picked up that phrase, 'In the name of Jesus, I plead the blood,' from those Pentecostals.

00:47:55.480 --> 00:47:57.552
And all through these years, I've always pled the blood in the name of Jesus.

00:47:57.552 --> 00:48:00.063
There's power in the blood.

00:48:00.063 --> 00:48:01.320
Glory to God.

00:48:01.320 --> 00:48:07.778
It worked quite well for me, and it'll work for you, too.

00:48:07.778 --> 00:48:09.040
There's power in the blood.

00:48:09.040 --> 00:48:17.509
As the Bible says, 'And they overcame him,' the devil, 'by or because of the blood of the Lamb and by the word of their testimony,' confession.

00:48:24.613 --> 00:48:24.900
The blood of Jesus Christ is precious because of its song-inspiring power.

00:48:27.200 --> 00:48:42.450
In Revelation 5:9 it says, 'And they sang a new song, saying, "Thou art worthy to take the book and to open the seals thereof, for thou wast slain and hast redeemed us to God by thy blood.

00:48:42.450 --> 00:48:45.594
Glory to God out of every kindred and tongue and people and nation.

00:48:45.594 --> 00:48:50.472
"' This is a new song for new souls and a new sphere.

00:48:50.472 --> 00:48:57.204
